<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>TSI 99-12-05 - Engine Control Module (ECM) Connector Sealing</stitle>
    <tsi id="tsi991205" tsitype="engine">
        <tsinumber>99-12-05</tsinumber>
        <tsidate>February, 1999</tsidate>
        <subjectfile>Engines</subjectfile>
        <subjectgroup>
            <subject>Engine Control Module (ECM) Connector Sealing</subject>
        </subjectgroup>
        <apply>
            <configure>
                <engfamgroup/>

                <engfam>T 444E</engfam>
                <engfam>DT 466E</engfam>
                <engfam>International&#174; 530E</engfam>
            </configure>
        </apply>
        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <title>ECM Connector Product Improvement</title>
                <para>When servicing the Diamond Logic&#8482; controller, the application of an approved dielectric
                    grease to the disconnected ECM connectors is encouraged. This action will provide a protective
                    moisture tight seal that ensures the ECM connectors will continue to perform effectively.
                </para>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
        <svcproc svcproctype="lubricate" graphiccount="0">
            <title>PARTS AFFECTED</title>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>ECM Connector (Wiring Harness Component)</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Diamond Logic&#8482; Controller</para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
        </svcproc>
        <svcproc svcproctype="lubricate" graphiccount="2">
            <title>INSPECTION PROCEDURE</title>
            <para>To provide moisture tight seal to ECM connectors, refer to the procedure below.</para>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>Use only recommended dielectric grease. Do not substitute with any other grease. The use of a
                        non-approved grease may damage connector components. Refer to Table 1
                        <hotlnk xrefid="t99120501">Dielectric Grease and Instruction Label
                            <xref refid="t99120501"/>.
                        </hotlnk>
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <seqlist>
                <item>
                    <para>Disconnect both ECM connectors from the Diamond Logic&#8482; controller.</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Apply a 3/8 inch bead of authorized dielectric grease to each ECM connector. Refer to Figure 1
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f99120501">Dielectric Grease Installation
                            <xref refid="f99120501"/>
                        </hotlnk>
                        . Begin applying dielectric grease from the bolt moving toward the ends of the ECM connectors.
                        Reinstall the ECM connectors into the Diamond Logic&#8482; controller. Refer to Figure 2
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f99120502">Reinstalling ECM Connector
                            <xref refid="f99120502"/>
                        </hotlnk>
                        . The dielectric grease will coat all the terminals and overflow on the sides of the connector
                        to produce a moisture tight seal.
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Tighten both connectors to 40 lb&#183;in. Disregard the 35 lb&#183;in torque specification
                        stamped on ECM connector.
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Apply Grease Instruction Label to identify that the ECM connectors and Diamond Logic&#8482;
                        controller has been serviced and sealed with the proper grease. Refer to Table 1
                        <hotlnk xrefid="t99120501" appearance="icon">Dielectric Grease and Instruction Label
                            <xref refid="t99120501"/>.
                        </hotlnk>
                    </para>
                </item>
            </seqlist>
            <table id="t99120501" frame="all">
                <title>Dielectric Grease and Instruction Label</title>
                <tgroup cols="3" colsep="1" rowsep="1">
                    <colspec colwidth="132*"/>
                    <colspec colwidth="132*"/>
                    <colspec colwidth="132*"/>
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry valign="top" align="center">
                                <para>Part Number</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry valign="top" align="center">
                                <para>Description</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry valign="top" align="center">
                                <para>Quantity</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry valign="top" align="center">
                                <para>1831731C1</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry valign="top" align="center">
                                <para>Dielectric Grease</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry valign="top" align="center">
                                <para>4 oz Tube</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry valign="top" align="center">
                                <para>1831730C1</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry valign="top" align="center">
                                <para>Dielectric Grease</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry valign="top" align="center">
                                <para>1/4 oz Tube</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry valign="top" align="center">
                                <para>1831746C1</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry valign="top" align="center">
                                <para>Grease Instruction Label</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry valign="top" align="center">
                                <para>1</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>1/4 oz tube of dielectric grease will service one ECM connector.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="f99120501" figsize="col-wide">
